<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Molas Pass</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[3,326 m alpine bowl with Grenadier Range across the valley. Photographers' favorite — wildflowers in July, aspen gold in late September.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-107.709000,37.747000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Silverton</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[1874 silver-mining town, gravel main streets preserved. Northern terminus of the Durango &amp; Silverton narrow-gauge steam railroad.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-107.664500,37.811900,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Red Mountain Pass</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[3,358 m. Iron oxide stains the surrounding peaks fluorescent orange. Avalanche country — dozens of named slide paths.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-107.711700,37.896400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Ironton ghost town</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Late-19th-century mining camp ruins; weathered timbers and rust-colored mine tailings.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-107.671100,37.934300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Bear Creek Falls</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[60 m falls drops from beneath the road right beside a turnout — no fence, just a step into the void.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-107.664400,37.996300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Ouray</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA['Switzerland of America,' set in a box canyon. Hot springs pool downtown; world's largest collection of frozen-waterfall ice climbing in winter.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-107.671700,38.022800,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
